            <title>[SPR-1134] lazy JMX connection</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-1134</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m using MBeanServerConnectionFactoryBean and MBeanProxyFactoryBean to access JMX MBeans from the client (like documented on chapter 20 of the manual)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My problem is that if the server isn&apos;t running, it fails with an exception. Is there any way to keep the configuration this way, but generate exceptions in runtime (when I want to call the proxy)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I had this same problem with the RMI exporter, but it had a lazy argument, I don&apos;t see one for the JMX setup.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
